1.164
log
@Document new KERN_NTHREADS and KERN_MAXTHREAD sysctls
@
text
@d1 1
a1 1
.\"	$OpenBSD: sysctl.8,v 1.163 2012/03/11 15:24:24 schwarze Exp $
d33 1
a33 1
.Dd $Mdocdate: March 11 2012 $
a84 1
.Pp
a509 13
.Pp
To adjust the number of kernel nfsio
threads used to service asynchronous
I/O requests on an NFS client machine:
.Pp
.Dl # sysctl vfs.nfs.iothreads=4
.Pp
The default is 4; 20 is the maximum.
See
.Xr nfssvc 2
and
.Xr nfsd 8
for further discussion.
@


